WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.445 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:05.445 --> 00:00:35.210 align:middle line:90%


00:00:35.210 --> 00:00:38.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Leaving behind everything
we thought we knew and diving

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:40.590 align:middle line:90%
into the unknown.

00:00:40.590 --> 00:00:43.280 align:middle line:84%
This is how our
investigation into fluoride

00:00:43.280 --> 00:00:47.450 align:middle line:84%
started, trying to forget any
preconceived ideas that we

00:00:47.450 --> 00:00:50.990 align:middle line:84%
had about what we thought
to be a safe product.

00:00:50.990 --> 00:00:54.850 align:middle line:84%
It was in the archives of the
Schneider Steelworks in Creusot

00:00:54.850 --> 00:00:57.110 align:middle line:84%
that we found the first
piece of evidence that

00:00:57.110 --> 00:01:03.830 align:middle line:84%
confirmed our worries, a report
from 1970 entitled "Pollution."

00:01:03.830 --> 00:01:07.100 align:middle line:84%
In the report, they
talk about fluoride,

00:01:07.100 --> 00:01:10.700 align:middle line:84%
a mineral used to melt
steam in the tall chimneys

00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:12.140 align:middle line:90%
and of toxic smoke.

00:01:12.140 --> 00:01:18.400 align:middle line:90%


00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:21.800 align:middle line:84%
We saw pictures of cows
with a mysterious illness,

00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:26.335 align:middle line:84%
fluorosis, an illness that is
apparently caused by fluoride.

00:01:26.335 --> 00:01:33.250 align:middle line:90%


00:01:33.250 --> 00:01:36.520 align:middle line:84%
In the surrounding
region, red puffs of smoke

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:40.210 align:middle line:84%
packed with fluoride filled
the sky before falling

00:01:40.210 --> 00:01:42.340 align:middle line:90%
into the fields below.

00:01:42.340 --> 00:01:46.150 align:middle line:84%
Few people remember this, except
for some elderly residents,

00:01:46.150 --> 00:01:49.390 align:middle line:84%
such as Francois
Drozdowsky, a retired

00:01:49.390 --> 00:01:52.930 align:middle line:84%
laborer at the steelworks
neighboring his house.

00:01:52.930 --> 00:02:18.640 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:02:18.640 --> 00:02:21.910 align:middle line:84%
>> How could a product that
appears harmless to most of us

00:02:21.910 --> 00:02:23.890 align:middle line:90%
turn out to be so noxious?

00:02:23.890 --> 00:02:25.180 align:middle line:90%
By aberration?

00:02:25.180 --> 00:02:26.900 align:middle line:90%
Turning a blind eye?

00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:29.860 align:middle line:84%
These questions form the
backbone of our investigation

00:02:29.860 --> 00:02:31.930 align:middle line:90%
in several countries.

00:02:31.930 --> 00:02:38.650 align:middle line:84%
France, the USA, England,
Germany, the Faroe Islands.

00:02:38.650 --> 00:02:42.340 align:middle line:84%
All around the world, people
were sounding the alarm,

00:02:42.340 --> 00:02:47.710 align:middle line:84%
but it was only in 2010 that the
WHO decided to class fluoride

00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:50.650 align:middle line:84%
among the 10 chemicals
that pose the greatest

00:02:50.650 --> 00:02:54.880 align:middle line:84%
threat to public health,
alongside asbestos, arsenic,

00:02:54.880 --> 00:02:57.140 align:middle line:90%
and dioxins.

00:02:57.140 --> 00:03:00.580 align:middle line:84%
It becomes toxic from
as little as 1 milligram

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:04.210 align:middle line:84%
per day for children
and 4 mg for adults.

00:03:04.210 --> 00:03:06.910 align:middle line:84%
And the maximum dose
is easily reached,

00:03:06.910 --> 00:03:10.150 align:middle line:84%
given the large number of
everyday products containing

00:03:10.150 --> 00:03:12.140 align:middle line:90%
fluoride.

00:03:12.140 --> 00:03:15.820 align:middle line:84%
What's more surprising
is, mixed with carbon gas,

00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:18.740 align:middle line:84%
you can find it in our frying
pans, our clothes, our pizza

00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:19.540 align:middle line:90%
boxes.

00:03:19.540 --> 00:03:22.390 align:middle line:90%


00:03:22.390 --> 00:03:26.380 align:middle line:84%
And even at a very low
dose, their toxicity

00:03:26.380 --> 00:03:29.920 align:middle line:84%
is considered to be extremely
concerning by scientists

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:30.920 align:middle line:90%
from around the world.

00:03:30.920 --> 00:03:42.160 align:middle line:90%


00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:45.870 align:middle line:84%
One professor, who knows more
than most about fluoride,

00:03:45.870 --> 00:03:48.290 align:middle line:90%
wrote her thesis on the topic.

00:03:48.290 --> 00:03:51.990 align:middle line:84%
Anne-Marie Musset heads one
of the biggest dental surgery

00:03:51.990 --> 00:03:53.463 align:middle line:90%
units in France.

00:03:53.463 --> 00:03:57.390 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:03:57.390 --> 00:03:59.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Here at the
University of Strasbourg,

00:03:59.700 --> 00:04:03.300 align:middle line:84%
the team often encounters
cases of fluoride poisoning,

00:04:03.300 --> 00:04:05.010 align:middle line:90%
and for a worrying reason.

00:04:05.010 --> 00:04:45.010 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:04:45.010 --> 00:04:48.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Professor Musset Knows
why the instruction to use

00:04:48.240 --> 00:04:52.440 align:middle line:84%
a pea-sized drop of toothpaste
was enforced on manufacturers

00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:55.680 align:middle line:84%
following a law
passed in March 2009.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:05:09.610 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:09.610 --> 00:05:12.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Fluorosis, that word again.

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:15.430 align:middle line:84%
This mysterious illness that
affected the [INAUDIBLE]

00:05:15.430 --> 00:05:20.040 align:middle line:84%
in Creusot in the 1970s,
also affects humans.

00:05:20.040 --> 00:05:24.950 align:middle line:84%
At very high doses, it leads
to serious skeletal problems.

00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:30.830 align:middle line:84%
At lower doses, it causes what
is known as dental fluorosis.

00:05:30.830 --> 00:06:02.490 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:06:02.490 --> 00:06:05.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Although fluoride is
supposed to protect your teeth,

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:08.610 align:middle line:84%
when it's ingesting in excess,
it has the opposite effect.

00:06:08.610 --> 00:06:11.550 align:middle line:90%


00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:15.530 align:middle line:84%
And the sources of fluoride
intoxication are numerous.

00:06:15.530 --> 00:06:19.770 align:middle line:84%
Fluoride is found in
lots of everyday things.

00:06:19.770 --> 00:06:25.880 align:middle line:84%
In lots of table
salts, in toothpaste,

00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:31.970 align:middle line:84%
in some bottled water, and
even sometimes in tap water.

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:34.790 align:middle line:90%


00:06:34.790 --> 00:06:39.120 align:middle line:84%
And you can very quickly exceed
the maximum recommended dose.

00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:44.630 align:middle line:84%
That's why since 2008 bottled
water containing more than 1.5

00:06:44.630 --> 00:06:47.720 align:middle line:84%
milligrams of fluoride
per liter are required

00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:50.300 align:middle line:84%
to print on the bottles
that the water is not

00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:54.360 align:middle line:84%
suitable for newborns or
children under seven years old.

00:06:54.360 --> 00:06:58.370 align:middle line:84%
We found six brands of
water, almost all sparkling,

00:06:58.370 --> 00:07:00.260 align:middle line:90%
that exceeded this limit.

00:07:00.260 --> 00:07:04.690 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:07:04.690 --> 00:07:07.880 align:middle line:84%
>> When Professor Musset sees
patients and feels that it is

00:07:07.880 --> 00:07:11.030 align:middle line:84%
necessary to prescribe them
fluoride to prevent dental

00:07:11.030 --> 00:07:14.150 align:middle line:84%
cavities, she systematically
undertakes an overview

00:07:14.150 --> 00:07:16.890 align:middle line:90%
of their fluoride consumption.

00:07:16.890 --> 00:08:16.280 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:08:16.280 --> 00:08:19.520 align:middle line:84%
>> In an ideal world, all
doctors would evaluate

00:08:19.520 --> 00:08:21.395 align:middle line:84%
their patients'
exposure to fluoride.

00:08:21.395 --> 00:08:24.020 align:middle line:90%


00:08:24.020 --> 00:08:27.290 align:middle line:84%
Rebecca would dry her eyes
after the scare of a visit

00:08:27.290 --> 00:08:30.590 align:middle line:84%
to the dentist, would go
home, and my investigation

00:08:30.590 --> 00:08:32.130 align:middle line:90%
would stop there.

00:08:32.130 --> 00:08:37.049 align:middle line:84%
But as you can imagine,
there's more to it than that.

00:08:37.049 --> 00:08:40.490 align:middle line:84%
The study, conducted a few
years ago by Professor Musset,

00:08:40.490 --> 00:08:43.590 align:middle line:84%
showed that in four to
12-year-olds, for example,

00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:47.210 align:middle line:84%
more than 40% of doctors
prescribe fluoride drops

00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:50.665 align:middle line:84%
without first evaluating
their exposure to fluoride.

00:08:50.665 --> 00:08:51.930 align:middle line:90%
And the result?

00:08:51.930 --> 00:09:17.450 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:09:17.450 --> 00:09:21.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Why are doctor so quick
to prescribe fluoride?

00:09:21.020 --> 00:09:23.240 align:middle line:90%
Through ignorance?

00:09:23.240 --> 00:09:26.870 align:middle line:84%
Unless they had been misled
by certain industrialists.

00:09:26.870 --> 00:09:29.420 align:middle line:90%


00:09:29.420 --> 00:09:33.320 align:middle line:84%
Industrialists, who, 50 years
ago, moved heaven and earth

00:09:33.320 --> 00:09:36.980 align:middle line:84%
to promote what was at first
just a cumbersome poison.

00:09:36.980 --> 00:09:48.320 align:middle line:90%


00:09:48.320 --> 00:09:54.500 align:middle line:84%
It was Alcoa who first brought
fluoride to fame in the 1930s.

00:09:54.500 --> 00:09:58.520 align:middle line:84%
At the time, the major
aluminum producer in the USA

00:09:58.520 --> 00:10:00.230 align:middle line:90%
had a serious problem.

00:10:00.230 --> 00:10:03.320 align:middle line:84%
They used fluoride
to extract aluminum,

00:10:03.320 --> 00:10:06.320 align:middle line:84%
but this process
produced toxic fumes.

00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:09.320 align:middle line:84%
The threat of a court
case hung over them.

00:10:09.320 --> 00:10:13.640 align:middle line:84%
In 1931, the company launched
a discreet investigation

00:10:13.640 --> 00:10:16.130 align:middle line:84%
into the cases of
dental fluorosis

00:10:16.130 --> 00:10:19.400 align:middle line:84%
that surrounded their
manufacturing plant in Messina,

00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:22.400 align:middle line:84%
in the north of the country,
and reported the results

00:10:22.400 --> 00:10:25.640 align:middle line:84%
in a confidential
internal letter.

00:10:25.640 --> 00:10:28.880 align:middle line:84%
"We have questioned three
of our local dentists

00:10:28.880 --> 00:10:32.090 align:middle line:84%
on the prevalence of
mottled enamel in Messina.

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.430 align:middle line:84%
All of the dentists
stated that they

00:10:34.430 --> 00:10:38.470 align:middle line:90%
have treated such cases here."

00:10:38.470 --> 00:10:42.670 align:middle line:84%
This letter has been read by
two men, Christopher Bryson,

00:10:42.670 --> 00:10:44.710 align:middle line:84%
an investigative
journalist who has spent

00:10:44.710 --> 00:10:48.670 align:middle line:84%
10 years of his life
researching the subject,

00:10:48.670 --> 00:10:52.030 align:middle line:84%
and Paul Connett, an
anti-fluoride activist

00:10:52.030 --> 00:10:55.570 align:middle line:84%
from the United States who
knows why Alcoa managed

00:10:55.570 --> 00:11:01.560 align:middle line:84%
to avoid any legal proceedings
due to the fluoride pollution.

00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:05.940 align:middle line:84%
>> The problem for industry
is, if your pollutant has

00:11:05.940 --> 00:11:11.730 align:middle line:84%
a biomarker, it's easier
to convince a jury that

00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:15.090 align:middle line:84%
the company is responsible
for this other damage.

00:11:15.090 --> 00:11:18.870 align:middle line:84%
The dental fluorosis would
not be a huge loss settlement,

00:11:18.870 --> 00:11:22.620 align:middle line:84%
but if you damage the person's
bones, if their arthritis,

00:11:22.620 --> 00:11:25.500 align:middle line:84%
or they've got bone
fractures, or other things

00:11:25.500 --> 00:11:28.140 align:middle line:84%
like lowering thyroid
function, then you're

00:11:28.140 --> 00:11:30.360 align:middle line:90%
into much higher settlements.

00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:33.270 align:middle line:84%
I think Alcoa knew
all of that the moment

00:11:33.270 --> 00:11:35.100 align:middle line:84%
that they found
that fluoride was

00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:37.230 align:middle line:90%
the cause of dental fluorosis.

00:11:37.230 --> 00:11:44.190 align:middle line:84%
>> In the aluminum factories,
fluoride was a killing poison.

00:11:44.190 --> 00:11:49.050 align:middle line:84%
It was causing workers all
sorts of health problems.

00:11:49.050 --> 00:11:53.040 align:middle line:84%
Around the aluminum
factories, animals and people

00:11:53.040 --> 00:11:54.660 align:middle line:90%
were being poisoned.

00:11:54.660 --> 00:11:59.700 align:middle line:84%
Alcoa needed a defense
against these actual lawsuits

00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:01.320 align:middle line:90%
and potential lawsuits.

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:06.060 align:middle line:84%
They needed something good
to say about fluoride.

00:12:06.060 --> 00:12:09.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Alcoa found the answer to
their problem at the Mellon

00:12:09.450 --> 00:12:13.440 align:middle line:84%
Institute, an applied science
laboratory in Pittsburgh that

00:12:13.440 --> 00:12:17.310 align:middle line:84%
the aluminum giants had created
themselves in order to serve

00:12:17.310 --> 00:12:20.440 align:middle line:84%
the interests of
the industrialists.

00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:23.880 align:middle line:84%
The Institute had already been
used to legitimize asbestos,

00:12:23.880 --> 00:12:25.580 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:28.790 align:middle line:84%
In 1935, a scientist
named Gerald Cox

00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:30.650 align:middle line:90%
was working at the Institute.

00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:35.090 align:middle line:84%
He was conducting a study on
teeth using laboratory rats.

00:12:35.090 --> 00:12:37.640 align:middle line:84%
One man came out of the
shadows to approach him.

00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:42.380 align:middle line:90%


00:12:42.380 --> 00:12:44.480 align:middle line:90%
He was called Francis Frary.

00:12:44.480 --> 00:12:47.390 align:middle line:84%
He was the research
director at Alcoa,

00:12:47.390 --> 00:12:51.440 align:middle line:84%
and he strongly suggested to Cox
that he should include fluoride

00:12:51.440 --> 00:12:53.510 align:middle line:90%
in his study.

00:12:53.510 --> 00:12:58.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Here we have the chief
chemist of Alcoa actually

00:12:58.010 --> 00:13:01.700 align:middle line:84%
suggesting to him, in
his animal experiments,

00:13:01.700 --> 00:13:06.560 align:middle line:84%
that he look into to see whether
fluoride was good for teeth.

00:13:06.560 --> 00:13:08.930 align:middle line:84%
So clearly they were
thinking we need

00:13:08.930 --> 00:13:12.860 align:middle line:84%
to find a beneficial
use for fluoride

00:13:12.860 --> 00:13:17.090 align:middle line:84%
to compensate for the
public's knowledge

00:13:17.090 --> 00:13:18.920 align:middle line:84%
that fluoride is
damaging health.

00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:21.920 align:middle line:90%
They needed--

00:13:21.920 --> 00:13:25.310 align:middle line:84%
>> The scientist from the
Mellon Institute made a mistake

00:13:25.310 --> 00:13:29.090 align:middle line:84%
in admitting that his study had
been influenced by Alcoa many

00:13:29.090 --> 00:13:31.910 align:middle line:84%
years later in correspondence
with a historian.

00:13:31.910 --> 00:13:34.990 align:middle line:90%


00:13:34.990 --> 00:13:38.080 align:middle line:84%
"The first time I ever
gave fluoride a thought

00:13:38.080 --> 00:13:40.000 align:middle line:84%
was in response to
a question posed

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:43.600 align:middle line:84%
by Dr. Francis Frary, director
of research for Alcoa."

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:47.200 align:middle line:90%


00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:49.630 align:middle line:90%
The poison had become a remedy.

00:13:49.630 --> 00:13:52.210 align:middle line:84%
Four years later,
the Mellon Institute

00:13:52.210 --> 00:13:54.430 align:middle line:84%
announced in a
scientific journal

00:13:54.430 --> 00:13:58.360 align:middle line:84%
that fluoride is the element
most probably responsible

00:13:58.360 --> 00:14:00.730 align:middle line:90%
for improved caries resistance.

00:14:00.730 --> 00:14:03.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Within a few
very short years,

00:14:03.430 --> 00:14:08.590 align:middle line:84%
triggered by the suggestion
of Francis Frary at Alcoa,

00:14:08.590 --> 00:14:13.150 align:middle line:84%
our perception of fluoride
goes from poison to something

00:14:13.150 --> 00:14:15.380 align:middle line:90%
that's good for teeth.

00:14:15.380 --> 00:14:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's how a sneaky
maneuver rewrote the history

00:14:18.890 --> 00:14:20.420 align:middle line:90%
of fluoride.

00:14:20.420 --> 00:14:24.140 align:middle line:84%
Nobody thought to
challenge it for decades.

00:14:24.140 --> 00:14:27.860 align:middle line:84%
After the war, it was used
in a number of products.

00:14:27.860 --> 00:14:33.695 align:middle line:84%
In the drinking water
of some countries,

00:14:33.695 --> 00:14:35.956 align:middle line:90%
in salt, in chewing gum.

00:14:35.956 --> 00:14:38.346 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:14:38.346 --> 00:14:45.040 align:middle line:90%


00:14:45.040 --> 00:14:48.850 align:middle line:84%
>> And of course, in toothpaste,
creating adverts that stuck

00:14:48.850 --> 00:14:51.250 align:middle line:90%
in the minds of generations.

00:14:51.250 --> 00:14:53.950 align:middle line:84%
Fluoride became a friend
who wished you well.

00:14:53.950 --> 00:15:02.200 align:middle line:90%


00:15:02.200 --> 00:15:06.880 align:middle line:84%
Even going as far as becoming
the way to find true love.

00:15:06.880 --> 00:15:10.117 align:middle line:84%
It's better to
laugh than to cry.

00:15:10.117 --> 00:15:12.512 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:15:12.512 --> 00:15:19.710 align:middle line:90%


00:15:19.710 --> 00:15:23.370 align:middle line:84%
>> France also prescribed
massive amounts of fluoride

00:15:23.370 --> 00:15:26.130 align:middle line:84%
to children in the
form of tablets,

00:15:26.130 --> 00:15:30.468 align:middle line:84%
and to infants in drops
to be taken from birth.

00:15:30.468 --> 00:15:32.948 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:15:32.948 --> 00:15:36.430 align:middle line:90%


00:15:36.430 --> 00:15:40.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Up until 2008, when professor
Goldberg and a few experts from

00:15:40.570 --> 00:15:43.660 align:middle line:84%
the French agency for the
security of health products

00:15:43.660 --> 00:15:45.790 align:middle line:84%
asked doctors, to
everyone's surprise,

00:15:45.790 --> 00:15:48.340 align:middle line:90%
to go against previous practice.

00:15:48.340 --> 00:16:25.840 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:29.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Calling into question
the quasi-religious belief

00:16:29.140 --> 00:16:31.870 align:middle line:84%
in fluoride was not
easy at the time,

00:16:31.870 --> 00:16:35.380 align:middle line:84%
and Professor Goldberg
didn't mince his words.

00:16:35.380 --> 00:16:47.400 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:16:47.400 --> 00:16:50.520 align:middle line:84%
>> But the medical profession
was not the only one to be

00:16:50.520 --> 00:16:51.750 align:middle line:90%
misled.

00:16:51.750 --> 00:16:54.210 align:middle line:84%
Certain health
authorities also showed

00:16:54.210 --> 00:16:57.030 align:middle line:84%
a certain laissez-faire
attitude towards this poison.

00:16:57.030 --> 00:17:04.410 align:middle line:90%


00:17:04.410 --> 00:17:07.200 align:middle line:84%
On a morning like this,
the Bordeaux vines

00:17:07.200 --> 00:17:11.700 align:middle line:84%
were bathed in sunlight by
the first rays of the day.

00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:14.010 align:middle line:84%
It is so beautiful
that we can almost

00:17:14.010 --> 00:17:18.869 align:middle line:84%
