for the Manhattan Project,

00:46:39.150 --> 00:46:41.340 align:middle line:84%
but serious medical
problems started

00:46:41.340 --> 00:46:44.430 align:middle line:84%
appearing wherever the
perfluorated compounds were

00:46:44.430 --> 00:46:46.460 align:middle line:90%
handled.

00:46:46.460 --> 00:46:51.620 align:middle line:84%
In this recently declassified
document from November 1944,

00:46:51.620 --> 00:46:55.370 align:middle line:84%
sent to Col. Warren, the leader
of the Manhattan Project,

00:46:55.370 --> 00:46:59.090 align:middle line:84%
the army worries that the
affair would be divulged.

00:46:59.090 --> 00:47:02.300 align:middle line:84%
"Some of these men were
definitely undesirable workers

00:47:02.300 --> 00:47:05.330 align:middle line:90%
on this particular project.

00:47:05.330 --> 00:47:08.450 align:middle line:84%
They have spread the word
that transfer to these areas

00:47:08.450 --> 00:47:12.570 align:middle line:84%
is more or less an exile
to Devil's Island."

00:47:12.570 --> 00:47:18.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Labor organizers and workers
were agitating because of how

00:47:18.480 --> 00:47:23.040 align:middle line:84%
many injuries there had been
and how scared the workers were

00:47:23.040 --> 00:47:26.730 align:middle line:84%
of handling these manifestly
dangerous chemicals.

00:47:26.730 --> 00:47:27.750 align:middle line:90%
There were deaths.

00:47:27.750 --> 00:47:29.220 align:middle line:90%
There were terrible burns.

00:47:29.220 --> 00:47:32.480 align:middle line:84%
There were exposures
on a very large scale.

00:47:32.480 --> 00:47:34.620 align:middle line:84%
DuPont were well
aware of how poisonous

00:47:34.620 --> 00:47:37.700 align:middle line:84%
the chemicals were that they
were using during World War II.

00:47:37.700 --> 00:47:42.470 align:middle line:90%


00:47:42.470 --> 00:47:45.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Since then, a lot of water
has passed under the bridge,

00:47:45.710 --> 00:47:50.020 align:middle line:84%
and Teflon has become a
beloved household name.

00:47:50.020 --> 00:47:53.630 align:middle line:84%
And then one day, studies
showed that cooking pans let out

00:47:53.630 --> 00:47:56.840 align:middle line:84%
toxic fumes at
high temperatures.

00:47:56.840 --> 00:48:03.230 align:middle line:84%
Yes, PFCs are everywhere, in our
pans, our duvets, our carpets,

00:48:03.230 --> 00:48:06.140 align:middle line:90%
in the air, in our water.

00:48:06.140 --> 00:48:09.440 align:middle line:84%
According to a study by the
American health authorities,

00:48:09.440 --> 00:48:13.010 align:middle line:84%
98% of Americans
have perfluorated

00:48:13.010 --> 00:48:14.310 align:middle line:90%
compounds in their blood.

00:48:14.310 --> 00:48:18.480 align:middle line:90%


00:48:18.480 --> 00:48:21.130 align:middle line:84%
And you don't need to
live next to a factory

00:48:21.130 --> 00:48:22.270 align:middle line:90%
to be contaminated.

00:48:22.270 --> 00:48:26.990 align:middle line:90%


00:48:26.990 --> 00:48:29.280 align:middle line:84%
The proof can be found
in a country that

00:48:29.280 --> 00:48:32.910 align:middle line:84%
should be free of all pollution,
in a corner of paradise.

00:48:32.910 --> 00:48:40.870 align:middle line:90%


00:48:40.870 --> 00:48:45.200 align:middle line:84%
It is probably one of the most
sumptuous places on the planet,

00:48:45.200 --> 00:48:48.730 align:middle line:84%
these lost islands
between the Norwegian sea

00:48:48.730 --> 00:48:53.290 align:middle line:84%
and the North Atlantic
Ocean, the Faroe Islands.

00:48:53.290 --> 00:48:56.470 align:middle line:84%
Life here would be peaceful
if scientists had not

00:48:56.470 --> 00:48:59.800 align:middle line:84%
found PFC in the blood
of most of the residents

00:48:59.800 --> 00:49:02.560 align:middle line:84%
of the archipelago,
including the children.

00:49:02.560 --> 00:49:07.170 align:middle line:90%


00:49:07.170 --> 00:49:08.800 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FAROESE]

00:49:08.800 --> 00:49:10.320 align:middle line:90%


00:49:10.320 --> 00:49:13.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Over five years, this
scientist studied the blood

00:49:13.200 --> 00:49:15.450 align:middle line:90%
of 650 children on the island.

00:49:15.450 --> 00:49:18.370 align:middle line:90%


00:49:18.370 --> 00:49:21.640 align:middle line:84%
Pal Weihe discovered a
manner of contamination

00:49:21.640 --> 00:49:23.200 align:middle line:90%
that he had never suspected.

00:49:23.200 --> 00:49:26.910 align:middle line:90%


00:49:26.910 --> 00:49:31.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Our surprise was that
breastfeeding was so important

00:49:31.690 --> 00:49:38.950 align:middle line:84%
for the actual concentration
of PFC in the child,

00:49:38.950 --> 00:49:45.360 align:middle line:84%
that breastfeeding was a
main contributor to the PFC

00:49:45.360 --> 00:49:50.260 align:middle line:84%
concentration in
the small children.

00:49:50.260 --> 00:49:53.620 align:middle line:84%
>> The deeper Pal Weihe
went into his study,

00:49:53.620 --> 00:49:56.770 align:middle line:84%
