became worrying.

00:49:56.770 --> 00:50:00.640 align:middle line:84%
He showed that the longer
women breastfed their child,

00:50:00.640 --> 00:50:04.030 align:middle line:84%
the higher the concentration
of perfluorated compounds

00:50:04.030 --> 00:50:05.620 align:middle line:90%
increased in the baby's blood.

00:50:05.620 --> 00:50:08.760 align:middle line:90%


00:50:08.760 --> 00:50:14.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Here's one with just
a short breastfeeding.

00:50:14.680 --> 00:50:16.870 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:50:16.870 --> 00:50:24.520 align:middle line:84%
And there the
concentration is only 5.3.

00:50:24.520 --> 00:50:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Let's take the person with the
longest duration of 12 months.

00:50:31.910 --> 00:50:34.630 align:middle line:84%
12 months of exclusive
breastfeeding, that person,

00:50:34.630 --> 00:50:35.950 align:middle line:90%
the first person here.

00:50:35.950 --> 00:50:40.060 align:middle line:84%
Let's go in and find what
the concentration of PFC

00:50:40.060 --> 00:50:43.530 align:middle line:90%
was in the blood of the child.

00:50:43.530 --> 00:50:48.210 align:middle line:90%
That was 10.1.

00:50:48.210 --> 00:50:51.720 align:middle line:90%
That is in the high level.

00:50:51.720 --> 00:50:55.800 align:middle line:84%
>> These results are concerning,
as the immune system is very

00:50:55.800 --> 00:50:59.160 align:middle line:84%
vulnerable in the first
few months of life.

00:50:59.160 --> 00:51:01.710 align:middle line:84%
Four years ago,
Pal Weihe conducted

00:51:01.710 --> 00:51:05.120 align:middle line:84%
a study looking at
children and PFCs,

00:51:05.120 --> 00:51:07.470 align:middle line:84%
and indeed showed
a stronger effect

00:51:07.470 --> 00:51:12.000 align:middle line:84%
on the organism's
defense mechanisms.

00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:18.390 align:middle line:84%
>> So for every doubling
of PFC at the age of five,

00:51:18.390 --> 00:51:22.140 align:middle line:84%
there was a reduction of about
50% of the antibody formation

00:51:22.140 --> 00:51:24.390 align:middle line:90%
at age seven.

00:51:24.390 --> 00:51:27.450 align:middle line:84%
We don't know, really,
what that means,

00:51:27.450 --> 00:51:30.150 align:middle line:84%
but it could be from
infectious diseases.

00:51:30.150 --> 00:51:32.660 align:middle line:90%


00:51:32.660 --> 00:51:35.280 align:middle line:84%
In the worst case
scenario, to take

00:51:35.280 --> 00:51:37.560 align:middle line:90%
cancer and autoimmune diseases.

00:51:37.560 --> 00:51:44.370 align:middle line:90%


00:51:44.370 --> 00:51:47.970 align:middle line:84%
>> This study was alarming
to the mothers on the island,

00:51:47.970 --> 00:51:52.080 align:middle line:84%
because here breastfeeding
is a religion.

00:51:52.080 --> 00:51:55.980 align:middle line:84%
97% of mothers
breastfeed their child.

00:51:55.980 --> 00:52:00.360 align:middle line:84%
Jonrit Halling breastfed
her two sons for a year.

00:52:00.360 --> 00:52:03.150 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FAROESE]

00:52:03.150 --> 00:52:06.080 align:middle line:84%
>> But for her third
child, who is on its way,

00:52:06.080 --> 00:52:09.696 align:middle line:84%
she is almost sure that
she won't do the same.

00:52:09.696 --> 00:52:12.225 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FAROESE]

00:52:12.225 --> 00:52:15.700 align:middle line:84%
>> I could not have done it
in another way back then,

00:52:15.700 --> 00:52:18.850 align:middle line:90%
because I didn't knew better.

00:52:18.850 --> 00:52:23.100 align:middle line:84%
But now I think
for my next child,

00:52:23.100 --> 00:52:26.190 align:middle line:84%
I will think about
how long I am going

00:52:26.190 --> 00:52:29.040 align:middle line:90%
to breastfeed, the duration.

00:52:29.040 --> 00:52:31.710 align:middle line:90%
At least four months, I think.

00:52:31.710 --> 00:52:34.770 align:middle line:90%
Maybe half year, but not longer.

00:52:34.770 --> 00:52:37.740 align:middle line:84%
>> A few years ago, Jonrit
Halling was able to have

00:52:37.740 --> 00:52:41.810 align:middle line:84%
