strongly rebuked by Greenpeace.

00:53:47.180 --> 00:53:50.620 align:middle line:84%
Through an international
campaign named Detox,

00:53:50.620 --> 00:53:54.740 align:middle line:84%
the ecologists attempted to
force both Adidas and Nike

00:53:54.740 --> 00:53:57.725 align:middle line:84%
from using dangerous
chemicals, including PFCs.

00:53:57.725 --> 00:54:08.660 align:middle line:90%


00:54:08.660 --> 00:54:11.510 align:middle line:84%
At the headquarters
of Adidas in Germany,

00:54:11.510 --> 00:54:13.790 align:middle line:84%
you won't find anybody
who will tell you

00:54:13.790 --> 00:54:17.060 align:middle line:84%
that it was this campaign
that led to the brand changing

00:54:17.060 --> 00:54:18.950 align:middle line:90%
its products.

00:54:18.950 --> 00:54:22.880 align:middle line:84%
But after all, does
it really matter?

00:54:22.880 --> 00:54:26.780 align:middle line:84%
The group was the first
to attack the use of PFCs.

00:54:26.780 --> 00:54:28.820 align:middle line:90%
That earned them a quick visit.

00:54:28.820 --> 00:54:32.250 align:middle line:90%


00:54:32.250 --> 00:54:35.040 align:middle line:84%
Steve Richardson has set
himself the challenge

00:54:35.040 --> 00:54:43.200 align:middle line:84%
